# GLC design system (V7 extract)

## Typography lock (non-negotiable)

- **Headings / display:** **Oswald** only (`--font-oswald` / `font-serif` per app setup). Section H2, 3-act headline, stat/card numerals follow the scales below.
- **Body, UI, labels:** **Barlow Condensed** for `font-label` and condensed UI tracks; longform body uses **Barlow** as the primary sans (`font-sans` in root layout). Do not substitute other display or condensed families.

## §6 — Typography architecture (readability-first)

Display and headings (Oswald):

- 3-Act Headline: `clamp(58px, 8vw, 118px)`; weights 200/600/700; tracking `-0.02em`.
- Stat number: `clamp(52px, 5vw, 80px)`; weight 700; tracking `-0.04em`.
- Card number: 64px; weight 700; tracking `-0.04em`.
- Section H2: `text-3xl → sm:text-4xl` (`clamp(36px, 3.5vw, 52px)`); weight 600; uppercase; tight leading/tracking.
- Card title / panel H3: 20px (`text-xl → sm:text-2xl`); weight 700; tracking `0.02em`; uppercase.

Metadata and labels (`font-label` → Barlow Condensed):

- Section labels / eyebrows: `font-label text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.14em] text-ink`.
- Side label: 9px; weight 800; tracking `0.22em`; uppercase.
- Tab labels: `font-label text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.14em] text-ink`.
- CTA primary: 12px or 13px; weight 700/800; tracking `0.08em`–`0.14em`; uppercase.
- Stat label: `font-label text-[11px] font-bold tracking-[0.14em] text-ink`.

Longform and UI copy:

- Intro/body: `text-[15px] leading-[1.72] text-ink sm:text-base` (15px floor).
- Card description: same as body standards.

## §7 — Interactive DNA and physics

- Reveal staging at viewport threshold 0.5: BG → eyebrow (0.4s) → headline (0.5–0.8s) → caption (1.15s) → CTA (1.9s).
- Section entrance: `view-reveal-up` (0.65s, `cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1)`, translateY 16→0); image parallax lag ~0.2s vs text when present.
- `pivot-expand-reveal`: 0.85s; 50% slide; 1.02× X scale tension.
- Accordion: 700ms width expansion; 220ms motif drift; `--ease-expo`.
- Tabs: `role="tablist"`; selected inversion; `[hidden]` on panels.
- Count-up: 1800ms cubic-out at 0.5 viewport threshold.
- `.cta-primary`: 0.2s envelope; hover `translateY(-2px)`; arrow `translateX(4px)`; brightness +10%.

## §8 — Visual hierarchy and palette

### Section composition (non-negotiable)

These rules apply to **every major section** (e.g. full-width `section-major`, hero bands, split CTAs). They were required in the legacy monolithic master spec but must be carried explicitly in modular rules.

**1. Minimum contrasting layers (≥3)**  
Stack **at least three visually distinct planes** so type and CTAs read clearly. Align with the Z-order vocabulary in `copy-writing.mdc` §1. Typical stack (pick **≥3** that contrast):

| Plane | Role | Examples |
|-------|------|----------|
| Base | Canvas | `band-light`, `band-dark`, `band-dark-field` |
| Substrate | Image or broad fill | `next/image` hero, tonal wash, gradient field |
| Treatment | Scrim / glass | Multi-stop gradient, `backdrop-blur-md`, `bg-[rgb(10,12,11,0.45)]` |
| Structure | Rails / seams | 4px `var(--y)` spine, `border-white/10`, `var(--g200)` |
| Interaction | Foreground UI | CTA cluster, `bespoke-surface` card, `z-10` content shell |

Pure flat single-fill sections without substrate/treatment/structure separation **do not** meet the standard unless you add at least rails + machined panel + base.

**2. Typography color (tri-tonal — required)**  
Every section’s type must implement **three distinct typographic color treatments** (primary / secondary / tertiary) per band:

- **Primary:** headings / key numerals — dark band: `text-white` or `text-[color:var(--y)]`; light band: `text-ink`.
- **Secondary:** body / lede — dark band: `text-white/90`; light band: `text-ink` or `--text-600` sparingly for supporting lines.
- **Tertiary:** eyebrows / metadata — dark band: `text-white/55`; light band: `text-ink-muted` / `text-400`.

Do not collapse eyebrow, headline, and body into one opacity or one gray.

**3. Minimum palette presence in section design (≥3 roles)**  
Beyond photo pixels, the **designed** UI must show **at least three** intentional GLC palette roles in the same section — for example:

- `--y` (rail, rule, stat numeral, gradient accent, or CTA fill), **and**
- `--ink` / dark glass (`rgb(10,12,11)`, `text-ink`), **and**
- White at a defined tier (`text-white`, `text-white/90`, `border-white/10`, or light panel `#fff`).

On **light** bands, substitute: `text-ink` + `--text-600` or muted label + `--y` accent. A section that is only white+gray with no yellow where an accent is expected is non-compliant.

Colors:

- `--yellow-core` / `--y`: `#f2b705`
- `--charcoal-deep` / `--ink`: `#1e1c1a`
- `--white`: `#ffffff`
- `--text-600`: `#6b6560` (sparingly; not default for labels/body)

Hero metrics cluster: yellow on numerals; `text-white/90` on stat labels; `text-white/55` on coverage/overline.

Depth and surfaces:

- `.bespoke-surface` + `.panel-machined` for machined depth.
- Glass panel: `bg-[rgb(10,12,11,0.45)]`, `backdrop-blur-md`, `border-white/10`.
- Borders: 4px yellow rails; 1px seams (`var(--g200)`); 1px section dividers.
- Shape: sharp industrial edges (`--radius: 0` baseline).

## Service photography — `public/images/services/`

Project photography is grouped **by service line**. When adding or referencing images, use the subfolder that matches the service (do not default to another line’s folder).

Root: `public/images/services/`

| Subfolder | Service line |
|-----------|----------------|
| `Drainage-and-Hardscaping` | Drainage & hardscaping |
| `Excavation` | Excavation |
| `Foundations` | Foundations |
| `Grading` | Grading |
| `Hauling` | Hauling |
| `Snow Removal` | Snow removal (folder name includes a space — encode as `%20` in public URLs, e.g. `/images/services/Snow%20Removal/…`) |

Prefer **`next/image`** with paths under `/images/services/…`. Filenames may include spaces or mixed case; encode path segments in URLs as needed.

## Globals checklist

Ensure `app/globals.css` / Tailwind expose: `font-label` → Barlow Condensed; yellow core token; dark glass RGB above; `.hero-stage` when staggered hero reveals are required.
